The paper deals with theoretical machine learning and the learnability of certain types of problems, which is a topic that falls under the umbrella of machine learning and artificial intelligence. Therefore, cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) are the most likely sub-categories. The paper also uses set-theoretic techniques to prove its results, which suggests that it could also be classified under cs.CC (Computational Complexity) and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). Finally, the paper deals with information theory and the limits of what can be learned, which could place it under cs.IT (Information Theory).
